<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="929" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d929">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Russell.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-04-07"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 104.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The mixed claims commission appointed by
                            the United States and Venezuela will assemble on the 1st day of June at
                            Caracas. I inclose two copies of the protocol,<note n="a" xml:id="d929fna">Printed in <ref target="frus1903#pg_804">Foreign
                                    Relations, 1903, page 804</ref>.</note> one for yourself and the
                            other for the Venezuelan foreign office. You will arrange with the
                            foreign office for suitable rooms in which the commission and its
                            personnel may perform their work.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>